.TH "CSSMEDIARULE" "3JS" "October 17, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CSSMediaRule \- CSSMediaRule
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]CSSMediaRule\f[B]\f[R] interface represents a single CSS
\f[CR]\(atmedia\f[R] rule.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]Inherits properties from its ancestors \f[CI]CSSConditionRule\f[I],
\f[CI]CSSGroupingRule\f[I], and \f[CI]CSSRule\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]CSSMediaRule.media\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]MediaList\f[R] representing the intended destination
medium for style information.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]No specific methods; inherits methods from its ancestors
\f[CI]CSSConditionRule\f[I], \f[CI]CSSGroupingRule\f[I], and
\f[CI]CSSRule\f[I].\f[R]
.SH EXAMPLES
The CSS below includes a media query with one style rule.
The MDN live sample infrastructure combines all the CSS blocks in the
example into a single inline style with the id \f[CR]css\-output\f[R],
so we first use \f[CR]document.getElementById()\f[R] to find that sheet.
\f[CR]myRules[0]\f[R] returns a \f[CR]CSSMediaRule\f[R] object, from
which we can get the \f[CR]mediaText\f[R].
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]p\f[R] id=\(dqlog\(dq></\f[B]p\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]\(atmedia\f[R] (\f[B]width\f[R] >= 500px) {
  body {
    \f[B]color\f[R]: blue;
  }
}
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] log = document.getElementById(\(dqlog\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] myRules = document.getElementById(\(dqcss\-output\(dq).sheet.cssRules;
\f[B]const\f[R] mediaList = myRules[0]; \f[I]// a CSSMediaRule representing the media query.\f[R]
log.textContent += \(ga ${mediaList.media.mediaText}\(ga;
.EE
